latestPosts.caption: Maybe being a girl dad in 2025 is giving your daughter the wings to fly 🚀
Still crushing on our swimwear launch! Check it out for unique swimsuits that make looking good on a vacation so much easier!

Only the best for our lovely community - swimwear that’s designed keeping their bodies and lives in mind. Say good bye to the awkwardness of finding swimwear perfect for the family Goa trip - checkout our NEWLY launched swimwear - complete with cover ups and still giving immaculate vibes.

8 months in the making - countless trials, fit checks and obsessing over the little things - we are so thrilled to bring you SWIMWEAR designed to make you look good and feel good. High coverage without being aunty, fun and flirty prints, strategic cutouts to make a basic one piece fun and INSPIRED cover up options that’ll seamlessly take you from beach to lunch. This is a collection that moves with you, fits in your carry on for a weekend Goa trip, and gives your vacation looks the glow up they needed!

If the last 2.5 years have taught me anything - it’s that anything worth building is a marathon and not a sprint. I’ve seen the follower count go up inch by inch, seen sales grown inch by inch, and gotten up everyday and gotten myself to work through all the curveballs that life has to throw. 

Many working Sundays, late nights, cancelled vacations, mishaps, missed targets later we are here. Half a million followers, profitable, bootstrapped, with a team of 100, fully women founded and run. 

No part of building a startup is glamorous. It’s a lot of headaches, messy problems, shoots in the sun, constant innovation and constant grind. Along the way though, we are able to offer employment directly to a 100 people and indirectly to many more 100s. We are able to bring positive change to their lives. We are able to make customers who proudly and happily wear our clothes feel a little bit brighter about their day. It’s been the journey of a lifetime and we have so many more miles to go! 

Cheers to the team, cheers to all the beautiful Indian women who trust us to dress them for their special and not so special moments - because the magic is created in the everyday.

My mom has two roles - mom at home and mom at Uptownie. 

8 years ago when the brand was a baby, my mom joined the team. At the age of 55 she took on a new challenge - to groom and grow Uptownie. Within a short period of time, she became the mom of the office - everyone’s one stop solution for all work related or even life related problems. Every work place strives to feel like a family but ours is truly just that thanks to my mom who brings the same relentless energy and care to the lives of everyone in the team that she has poured into mine and my sisters’ lives. There is no one’s birthday for whom the office cheers louder or whose presence is missed more than my mom’s. 

But more than that, she single handedly runs our factory. She knows every fabric vendor and their families by name, has built such solid relationships with all our suppliers and vendors that they are willing to move mountains to prioritize our requirements in times of need and is so efficient about our production that we are able to deliver a quality product at an unbeatable price. 

She is also our greatest critic - from making us reshoot our reels when they don’t meet her standards, to motivating us to work when we flag she has always dreamt big dreams for us. This Mother’s Day cheers to my mom - who somehow has the energy for her two demanding daughters and also for the 100 plus Uptownie employees who are part of her large and adopted family!

latestPosts.caption: When we first launched our bubble skirts I was super excited. I loved the trend, had tried many available in the market and didn’t think any of them really worked. Either the length was TOO micro mini, or the fabric was polyester and uncomfortable or the colours weren’t versatile enough. So we made our own - short but not obnoxiously so, with cute bows and short shorts inside to make it comfortable to wear. But we launched too late - and instead of selling 200 pieces a day we sold 20 because the trend was already on its way out. Luckily we do small batch production to test our products but it was a brutal reminder that the fashion business moves fast and to do well you have to delivery a hot product that feels good and is priced right and also hits the market at just the right time!

latestPosts.caption: Walk before you run … an evergreen lesson in life and entrepreneurship 🤷‍♀️! Trying to share my failures publicly so that you don’t fall into the same ditches!

Building a profitable fashion brand is all about viral products that spark what every brand wants - organic word of mouth marketing! Our insta famous heart shirt helped us break into the millennial customer segment and told our customers - Uptownie looks really good but feels even better!

Don’t sit like a girl - just wear clothes that are made to make your life easier! Mindful design means standing in the shoes of the customer and making every effort to make their lives simpler and more comfortable without compromising on the look! Uptownie’s all about mindful design meeting global trends 💫
